
Klaviyo Email Design & Content Instructions Map

A reusable framework for creating consistent, conversion-driven Klaviyo emails across all flows and campaigns.

This document establishes design, structure, and brand-experience rules to ensure every email (flow or campaign) is on-brand, readable, accessible, mobile-optimized, and revenue-focused.

Use this as your go-to reference whenever building or optimizing emails inside Klaviyo.

⸻

1. Global Email Structure Standards

1.1 Layout Structure

Every email should follow this hierarchy unless otherwise specified:
	1.	Hero Section
	•	Clear headline
	•	Sub-headline
	•	Primary CTA
	•	Branded imagery
	2.	Value Section
	•	1–3 supporting points
	•	Icons, product photos, or lifestyle shots
	3.	Social Proof
	•	Testimonials, reviews, ratings, or press badges
	4.	Secondary CTA
	•	Reinforce main outcome or objection removal
	5.	Footer
	•	Links to shop, categories, customer service, social

