3. Email Component Library

These are standard modules your team should reuse for consistency and speed:

Hero Variants
	•	Product-led hero
	•	Offer-driven hero
	•	Storytelling hero
	•	Founder letter hero (with portrait)

Content Blocks
	•	Feature list (3-up or 4-up)
	•	Ingredients/benefits block
	•	Before/after comparison
	•	Review testimonial carousel
	•	Social proof wall
	•	FAQ accordion
	•	“Complete the routine” or cross-sell module

Shopping Blocks
	•	Recommended products
	•	Bestsellers
	•	“People also buy”
	•	Collection highlight
	•	Cart reminders with dynamic blocks

Footer Templates
	•	Basic
	•	Full navigation
	•	Compliance-heavy (SMS/email consent)

⸻

4. CTA Rules & Best Practices

Primary CTA Format
	•	Clear, concise, action-oriented
	•	High-contrast button color
	•	Use no more than 1 main CTA per screen section

Examples:
“Shop Now”
“Take the Quiz”
“Claim Your Offer”
“Finish Checking Out”

Secondary CTA Format
	•	Text link
	•	Smaller button
	•	Soft intent

Examples:
“Learn More”
“See How It Works”
“View All Products”

⸻

5. Content Voice & Tone Guidelines

5.1 Standard Email Tone

(Replace this section with your client’s voice guide)
	•	Conversational
	•	Benefit-led
	•	Friendly, not fluffy
	•	Clear, not clever
	•	Value-first, then call-to-action

5.2 Copy Structure Rules
	•	Subject line: curiosity + clarity
	•	Preheader: don’t repeat the subject
	•	Headline: 6–10 words max
	•	Subheadline: supports the big idea
	•	Paragraphs: 1–3 lines only
	•	Use bullets for scannability
	•	Always close with a CTA + reminder

⸻

6. Klaviyo Email-Specific Rules

6.1 Mobile Optimization

Required:
	•	Min 14px body text
	•	Buttons 44px high
	•	600px max email width
	•	Avoid small tappable elements
	•	Keep headlines readable on mobile hero crops

6.2 Image Standards
	•	Max 1.2MB
	•	JPG for lifestyle
	•	PNG for transparent product assets
	•	Background-safe text for dark mode

6.3 Personalization Standards

Common dynamic tags:
	•	{{ first_name|default:‘Friend’ }}
	•	{{ organization|default:’’ }}
	•	Product recommendation blocks
	•	Abandoned cart dynamic content
	•	Review pull-ins (Yotpo/Judge.me)

6.4 Compliance
	•	CAN-SPAM
	•	SMS compliance language
	•	Unsubscribe link visible
	•	Mailing address visible

⸻

7. Flow-Specific Requirements

7.1 Welcome Series
	•	Strong hero introduction
	•	Big promise → product proof
	•	Social proof early
	•	Link to quiz or bestseller
	•	1–2 CTAs max
	•	Include a “why us” block in at least 1 email

7.2 Abandon Cart / Checkout
	•	Product image mandatory
	•	Speed-focused copy
	•	Trust badges
	•	Remove friction: shipping, returns, guarantee
	•	2–3 reminder touchpoints

7.3 Post-Purchase
	•	Congrats hero
	•	“What’s next” section
	•	Education on use-case
	•	Cross-sell intelligently
	•	Delivery timeline expectations

7.4 Winback
	•	Soft tone → not guilt-driven
	•	New arrivals or updated benefits
	•	Social proof from long-term users

7.5 VIP
	•	Exclusive tone
	•	Tier-based access
	•	Early-release hero
	•	Loyalty-driven CTAs

⸻

8. Offer & Promo Guidelines

Types of Offer Blocks
	•	% off
	•	Free gift
	•	Bundle savings
	•	Subscription benefits
	•	Tiered offers

Visual Rules
	•	Offer must be above the fold
	•	Large, bold offer text
	•	Countdown timers (only when true scarcity exists)
	•	Clear expiration language

⸻

9. Email Quality Checklist

Before publishing, ensure your email passes these checks:

Design
	•	Clear visual hierarchy
	•	Buttons high contrast
	•	Images cropped correctly on mobile
	•	Footer branded & compliant

Copy
	•	Subject line + preheader aligned
	•	No large text blocks
	•	Benefits highlighted
	•	Proof included

Above-the-Fold Rules
	•	CTA visible immediately on desktop
	•	CTA visible immediately on mobile
	•	No large image blocks before CTA

Image Optimization
	•	All images compressed
	•	JPG when possible
	•	No large images used unnecessarily
	•	Total HTML size tested for Gmail clipping
	•	Alt text added for accessibility

Technical
	•	UTM parameters added
	•	All links functional
	•	Alt text added
	•	dark mode friendly
	•	Mobile preview tested

Klaviyo-Specific
	•	Personalization tags validated
	•	Dynamic blocks rendering correctly
	•	Flow filters correct (if in automation)

⸻

10. Maintenance & Review

Monthly
	•	Update templates with design improvements
	•	Run mobile tests
	•	Refresh social proof modules
	•	Add seasonal hero variants

Quarterly
	•	Audit all flows for brand alignment
	•	Identify outdated offers, images, or modules
	•	Refresh testimonials and bestsellers
	•	Re-test top subject lines

⸻

11. Quick Reference: What to Use When

When writing a Welcome email:
→ Use brand story hero + “why people love us” blocks

When writing an Abandoned Cart email:
→ Use product hero + trust builder section + urgency

When writing a Post-Purchase email:
→ Use educational block + product usage tips + reorder CTA

When writing a Promo email:
→ Use offer hero + benefit stack + timer

When writing a Newsletter:
→ Use storytelling intro + product tie-in + soft CTA

